76561198063300799,Recommended,289600,35252155,Posted: 27 September,all,ChaseP.Perry,"This game is wonderful, and there is a lot of things that kept me coming back and playing it.Pros:> Semi-gun porn (attachments and ammo variants)> Squad based (Possible to Lone Wolf)> Witty dialogue> Great atmosphere> Decent Story> Cool gun mechanics> Pauseing system> Many different ways to play in terms of tactics and loadouts> Shotguns that use buckshot have a realistic range (quite effective against non-armored enemies)> Grenades are legit threat> Semi smart AICons:> Muddy graphics> Semi smart AI> Pause system is annoying unless you go to settings and adjust it> Can be buggy> Quests are often ill-explained in journal (so pay attention!)> Small pool of firearms (Mainly limited to Warsaw Pact firearms, and mainly the popular ones)> There are three levels that are annoyingly hard> Steep learning curveAll in all, its a good game for $9.99. If you enjoy real-time tactical games like Jagged Alliance then this game is for you. Take some time and explore the game's mechanics. I discovered that you could click and drag to make a ""field of suppression"" with fully-auto guns. Heck, unlike Jagged Alliance where fully auto guns fire in bursts, you can make your guy empty his ENTIRE mag into something (pray he doesnt miss). Its a game to adapt to, yes, but it sure is fun!"
,Not Recommended,289600,35041353,Posted: 18 September,all,Verdantil,"Tags: TacticalAdditional Tags: Delete Local Content & Remove from Library (3.8 Gigs)TLDR: Broken camera controls. Intro cutscene froze while the audio kept playing. Engine queues all inputs and impements them with a delay, often causing huge clusterflocks. Game's process stays open in background after exiting game.Original voice acting with subtitles was very nice, the russian voice acting sounded badass and fit pretty well with the dopey in-game models. Problem is the engine has a ton of issues. I cant rotate the camera. Using keyboard to just pan the camera around is choppy and stops responding almost immediately. Inching the camera forward to the first enemy I tested the combat. It constantly auto-pauses. There is not much you can do but get in range and click to shoot. The game would sort of put all inputs in an invisible queue and when trying to interact (e.g. change weapons) I could queue up a dozen commands and I would see my character then spaz out and change weapons a dozen times... I dont think the engine is up to the task to provide a clean and tactical game... Its a shame too because the minimap was well detailed and the game had some character with the story and setting, characters seemed somewhat believable but those are not enough on their own to save the experience."
